Node.Notes: Offering of animals that were burned completely on the altar (except the skin went to the priest; Lev 7:8).
Offerings where animal not burned, but divided among the priests and worshippers. Generally not imposed by regulations except for the Nazirite (Nu6:17) and the Feast of Tabernacles (Nu29:39–40).
Uncertain. Apparently the pronouns indicate not to build stone altars with dressed stones because the use of a tool on a stone to make it a dressed stone defiles it.
